      <hedline>
        <hl1>What to Look For in a Senator From New York</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert Freedman letter holds Hillary Rodham Clinton would bring to Senate 'prestige and clout' that Repr Rick A Lazio 'can only dream of' (Oct 22 editorial)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Hillary Clinton for the Senate'' (editorial, Oct. 22): As in the race between Robert F. Kennedy and a well-regarded Republican, Mrs. Clinton will bring to the Senate prestige and clout that Rick A. Lazio can only dream of.</p>
        <p>ROBERT FREEDMAN  Boston, Oct. 22, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
